On Thu, Mar 16, 2000 at 03:32:41PM +0800, liuxgmail wrote:
> Hi all,
>    I often compiled the linux kernel these days. I want to know
> how can I config the kernel to only compile the changed files.
> It's so tired to compiled all kernel files.
Well it just does... including all files that depend on the changed
files (which can be all if some essential headers are changed).
I recommend you read up on make dependencies. The make info pages
might be a good start.
